Soavi, from Chris Marker to the newest thresholds of contemporary film. These filmmakers battle the greatest odds a modern artist can face: the opposition of mass culture at large and a medium that requires enormous expenditures in every stage of production and distribution. Naturally, the average American moviehead rarely gets a chance to see these marginalized directors' work and often knows about them only through dazzled rumors and rhapsodic hearsay. Whimsical and deeply subjective, the viewpoints and evangelisms in Exile Cinema will serve as salve for the cineaste's lonesome fury.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 4aFilm, Visual Culture, and Performing Arts : Film Studies. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh1 aAndrew, Geoff, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAtkinson, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAtkinson, Michael, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aAufderheide, Patricia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCheshire, Godfrey, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClover, Joshua, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFuller, Graham, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHalter, Ed, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHampton, Howard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKite, B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKlawans, Stuart, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLim, Dennis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMaddin, Guy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcDonagh, 